                            <comment id="14028004" author="cheolsoo" created="Wed, 11 Jun 2014 17:51:45 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;This is great! Thank you for working on this.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Btw, does this jira depends on &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/TEZ-710&quot; title=&quot;Get Tez Local-mode work&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;TEZ-710&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;TEZ-710&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;? If so, can you link them together?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14028115" author="airbots" created="Wed, 11 Jun 2014 18:54:19 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=cheolsoo&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;cheolsoo&quot;&gt;Cheolsoo Park&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;br/&gt;
Thank you for assigning this to me. &lt;br/&gt;
Yes, it is, I will link them together.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14069103" author="airbots" created="Mon, 21 Jul 2014 20:35:01 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;updated according to latest pig. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14083189" author="daijy" created="Sat, 2 Aug 2014 00:36:33 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;A small fix to improve the usability. User don&apos;t need to set PIG_CLASSPATH and tez.lib.uris when using tez_local.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14085132" author="daijy" created="Mon, 4 Aug 2014 20:15:41 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Another update after &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/TEZ-1343&quot; title=&quot;Bypass the Fetcher and read directly from the local filesystem if source vertex ran on the same host&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;TEZ-1343&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;TEZ-1343&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; check in. Now tez local mode should work in most cases. &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=sseth&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;sseth&quot;&gt;Siddharth Seth&lt;/a&gt; also point out if Pig submit multiple DAG simultaneously, local mode will fail. But what we have right now is already very useful, so I would like to check this in and improve over time.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14085185" author="airbots" created="Mon, 4 Aug 2014 20:52:20 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;multiDAG will be considered in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/TEZ-1376&quot; title=&quot;Investigate independent parallel DAGs execution in Local Mode&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;TEZ-1376&quot;&gt;TEZ-1376&lt;/a&gt;. Thank you &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=daijy&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;daijy&quot;&gt;Daniel Dai&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=cheolsoo&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;cheolsoo&quot;&gt;Cheolsoo Park&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14085538" author="daijy" created="Tue, 5 Aug 2014 01:13:21 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Patch committed to trunk. Thanks &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=airbots&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;airbots&quot;&gt;Chen He&lt;/a&gt;!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
